# HR Analytics Using SQL

## Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing HR data using SQL to extract meaningful business insights that support workforce planning and human resource decision-making. The analysis explores employee demographics, department distribution, performance, engagement, satisfaction, training, and attrition through a series of business-oriented SQL queries.

The project demonstrates proficiency in SQL by solving real-world HR business problems using data exploration, aggregation, window functions, common table expressions (CTEs), subqueries, and views.

## Objectives

* Analyze employee distribution across departments and business units.
* Evaluate employee performance and engagement.
* Assess employee satisfaction and work-life balance.
* Examine training costs and participation.
* Identify workforce trends and potential areas for improvement.
* Generate actionable business insights using SQL.

## Dataset

The dataset contains employee information, including:

* Employee demographics
* Department and business unit
* Performance ratings
* Engagement and satisfaction scores
* Work-life balance
* Training details and costs
* Employment status
* Employee ratings

